http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Insurance-cover-for-coir-workers/article13991469.ece

The Kerala Coir Workers Welfare Fund Board will launch an insurance scheme for workers.The scheme, Coir Workers Suraksha Bima Yojna, is being implemented with contributions from workers and the government, in association with the Life Insurance Corporation of India. Over one lakh workers are expected to benefit from the scheme in the initial phase.The State-level inauguration of the scheme will be done by Minister for Coir Adoor Prakash at Haripad on Sunday. He will sign a memorandum of understanding with the LIC on the occasion.